
COPY AND ADAPT

MOTIVATION:
When writing tests for a new method, it
is common to copy and adapt an existing test case for
similar/sibling methods. Due to time constraints, developers
cannot spend time rewriting similar test cases from scratch.

MECHANICS:
- Look for code elements similar to the code element that
needs to be tested. A code element can be a class or a
method that already has associated test cases.
- Copy and paste the test case found for similar code
elements creating a new test case.
- Change the name of the pasted test case to reflect the
intent of the code element to be tested.
- Adapt the body of the pasted test case to comply with the
right entity types, parameter values, name conventions,
and context.


